						<summary>

						<p>Slab lying on the hillock west of the tank.</p>						

						<p>Telugu Chōḷa, Tirukālatidēva-Chōḍa Mahārāju.</p>						

						<p>This is dated <hi rend="bold">Śaka 1153, Nandana,</hi> corresponding to 1231 A.D.</p>						

						<p>Mutilated. It seems to record the gift of 10 <hi rend="italic">puṭṭis</hi> of land and 2 <hi rend="italic">vaṭṭlu</hi> of land situated on the west of Madanu Kummarapaṭi and yandaḍi and also land situated on the backside of Kāṭama-reḍḍi Kuṇṭa to Śrī Rāmadēva, Sigapaḷa and Villinambi. It also records the maintaining the some evening lamp <hi rend="italic">(sandhyādīpa)</hi> to the god Rāmadēva.</p>						

						</summary>
